On Monday, July 28, 2003, at 02:10 PM, Chris Mills wrote:

>> Now that I know how to remove the chrome trim around the beltline, my 
>> next
>> question is how does the sliding door remove?  Also. how heavy is it?
>
> Remove the trim over the slider track behind the slider door. Two 
> screws - one at each end of the trim piece. Large Phillips.
>
> Knock this piece of trim upward with rubber mallet to remove.
